
Overview of verb unwind

The verb unwind has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) unwind, wind off, unroll -- (reverse the winding or twisting of; "unwind a ball of yarn")
2. unwind, disentangle -- (separate the tangles of)
3. relax, loosen up, unbend, unwind, decompress, slow down -- (become less tense, rest, or take one's ease; "He relaxed in the hot tub"; "Let's all relax after a hard day's work")
4. relax, unstrain, unlax, loosen up, unwind, make relaxed -- (cause to feel relaxed; "A hot bath always relaxes me")
